From: Robert B Tesh <rtesh@utmb.edu> [edited]


Re: ProMED-mail Newcastle disease, wild birds - USA (03): (TX) dove 20121023.1358023
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Over the 10 years that we have tested dead birds from Harris County [Texas], we have made isolations of Newcastle disease virus every year.

The infected birds are always doves. Various species: mourning dove (_Zenaida macroura_), Eurasian collared dove (_Streptopelia decaocto_), and rock dove (_Columbia livia_) (published in the J Clin Microbiol 46:3303-3310).

--
Robert B Tesh, MD
University of Texas Medical Branch
USA
<rtesh@utmb.edu>

[Thanks Dr Tesh for your contribution.

The paper mentioned in Dr Tesh's comment is available at http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2566108/.

